author: @physicsfaith
text: I don't know if this gets fixed later in the video but there is a problem with the converted dates. He started off with ddmmyy format in Date when it was an object format. He ran pd.to_datetime which has converted it to yyyymmdd format. When you look, at 15:41 for example, you can see that it converted the Jan 2, 2018 date (the second data row) to 2018-02-01, which is Feb 1, 2018. If you doubt that look at row 3239. The date is 2020-12-16. The middle value is the month, not the day that he claims. So the time series is now all jumbled up in addition to having the wrong dates.
